server-config') as DevServerConfig;\n    93→    expect(config.assetPaths).toEqual([]);\n    94→  });\n    95→});\n    96→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PvKecRitjAEtEysUd4PffT","session_id":"866c9e5d-530c-4633-b303-286297fdf57e","uuid":"3202e0fe-49bc-4a9e-8190-6549ae53514f"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PvKecRitjAEtEysUd4PffT","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture of the codebase. Let me create a comprehensive summary document for you.\n\n---\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE CODEBASE ANALYSIS\n\n### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── index.ts           (exports main API)\n│   │   ├── types.ts           (interface definitions)\n│   │   ├── engine.ts          (BuildEngine class)\n│   │   └── templates.ts       (template factories)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts           (15 core tests)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── .eslintrc.cjs\n└── TASK.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. PLUGIN INTERFACE (src/core/types.ts)\n\n**Key Interfaces:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;           // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts)\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class orchestrates the build process:\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)` - adds plugins to the engine\n- `registerTemplate(template: Template)` - registers templates\n- `resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]` - topological sort to determine plugin execution order\n  - Validates no circular dependencies\n  - Validates all dependencies are registered\n  - Throws errors if validation fails\n- `async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>` - executes the full build:\n  1. Calls `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n  2. Calls `transformContent` hooks on all files\n  3. Renders templates and populates `ctx.output`\n  4. Calls `afterBuild` hooks in order\n\n**Build Flow:**\n```\nInput Files → beforeBuild → transformContent → Render Templates → afterBuild → Output\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. CORE TESTS (tests/core.test.ts) - 15 Tests\n\nAll 15 existing tests must continue to pass:\n\n1. **registers plugins** - plugin registration\n2. **registers templates** - template registration\n3. **builds with default template and renders HTML** - full build with template\n4. **builds with list template and renders list HTML** - list template rendering\n5. **outputs raw content when no matching template** - fallback behavior\n6. **calls plugin beforeBuild hook** - beforeBuild execution\n7. **calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files** - transformContent execution\n8. **calls plugin afterBuild hook** - afterBuild execution\n9. **executes plugins in dependency order** - DAG topological sort\n10. **throws on circular dependency** - error handling for cycles\n11. **throws on missing dependency** - error handling for missing deps\n12. **applies multiple plugins transformContent in order** - correct ordering\n13. **provides shared data store in build context** - ctx.data sharing\n14. **retains file metadata through build** - metadata preservation\n15. **produces empty output for empty file list** - edge case\n\n---\n\n### 5. PLUGIN TEST FILES AND REQUIREMENTS\n\n#### **WAVE 1 (No Dependencies)**\n\n**5.1. markdown-ext Plugin** (8 tests)\n- **Export:** `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` → `Plugin`\n- **Hook:** `transformContent` (async or sync)\n- **Requirements:**\n  - Convert basic markdown to HTML (using `marked` library)\n  - Handle footnotes with `[^1]` syntax:\n    - Replace `[^1]` with `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n    - Render footnote section at bottom: `<section class=\"footnotes\"><li id=\"fn-1\">...</li></section>`\n  - Handle admonition containers (`:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip`):\n    - Parse triple-colon syntax and convert to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-TYPE\">CONTENT</div>`\n  - Preserve existing HTML content\n  - Handle empty content gracefully\n\n**5.2. asset-pipeline Plugin** (8 tests)\n- **Export:** `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` → `Plugin`\n- **Hook:** `transformContent` (async or sync)\n- **Requirements:**\n  - Rewrite relative asset URLs:\n    - `src=\"./image.png\"` → `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n    - `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` → `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n  - Leave absolute URLs unchanged (http/https)\n  - Generate asset manifest in `ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', { assets: string[] })`\n  - Track all discovered assets\n  - Don't double-process already-rewritten URLs (starting with `/assets/`)\n\n**5.3. syntax-highlight Plugin** (8 tests)\n- **Export:** `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()` → `Plugin`\n- **Hook:** `transformContent` (async or sync)\n- **Requirements:**\n  - Add `highlighted` class to code blocks with language:\n    - Match `<pre><code class=\"language-LANG\">` and transform to include `highlighted`\n  - Add `data-language=\"LANG\"` attribute to `<pre>` tags\n  - Extract language from `class=\"language-LANG\"`\n  - Only process blocks WITH a language class\n  - Don't modify inline `<code>` tags (only `<pre><code>`)\n  - Handle empty code blocks\n  - Handle multiple code blocks in one file\n\n**5.4. taxonomy Plugin** (9 tests)\n- **Export:** `createTaxonomyPlugin()` → `Plugin`\n- **Hooks:** `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild`\n- **Requirements:**\n  - In `beforeBuild`:\n    - Build tag index: `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', Map<string, ContentFile[]>)`\n    - Extract tags from `file.tags` array\n    - Normalize tags to lowercase\n    - Store all files with each tag\n  - In `afterBuild`:\n    - Generate tag page HTML for each tag\n    - Store in `ctx.output` as `tags/TAG.html`\n    - List all files with that tag on the page\n  - Handle files without tags\n  - Handle case normalization (JavaScript → javascript)\n\n#### **WAVE 2 (Depend on Wave 1)**\n\n**5.5. rss-feed Plugin** (8 tests)\n- **Export:** `createRssFeedPlugin()` → `Plugin`\n- **Dependencies:** `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`\n- **Hook:** `afterBuild`\n- **Requirements:**\n  - Generate RSS 2.0 XML feed: `feed.xml`\n  - Valid RSS structure with `<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>` tags\n  - Feed items contain:\n    - `<title>` from file.title\n    - `<description>` with CDATA wrapped HTML content\n    - `<link>` to file (baseUrl + slug + .html)\n    - `<category>` tags from taxonomy (one per tag)\n    - `<pubDate>` if file.date exists\n  - Channel title from `config.title`\n  - Channel link from `config.baseUrl`\n  - Sort items by date newest first\n  - Handle files without dates (don't output `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>`)\n\n**5.6. search-index Plugin** (7 tests)\n- **Export:** `createSearchIndexPlugin()` → `Plugin`\n- **Dependencies:** `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`\n- **Hook:** `afterBuild`\n- **Requirements:**\n  - Generate `search-index.json`\n  - JSON array of objects with:\n    - `slug: string`\n    - `title: string`\n    - `content: string` (plain text, HTML stripped)\n    - `tags?: string[]` (optional, if present)\n  - Strip all HTML tags from content\n  - Include code block content\n  - Valid JSON\n  - Handle empty file list (return `[]`)\n\n#### **WAVE 3 (Depend on Wave 2)**\n\n**5.7. sitemap Plugin** (8 tests)\n- **Export:** `createSitemapPlugin()` → `Plugin`\n- **Dependencies:** `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`\n- **Hook:** `afterBuild`\n- **Requirements:**\n  - Generate `sitemap.xml`\n  - Valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>`, `<urlset>`, `<url><loc>`, `</urlset>`\n  - Include all content pages from `ctx.output` (*.html files)\n  - Include all tag pages from taxonomy (tags/*.html)\n  - Include feed.xml URL\n  - Use `config.baseUrl` for all URLs\n  - Complete URLs: `https://example.com/post-1.html`\n\n**5.8. dev-server Plugin** (9 tests)\n- **Export:** `createDevServerPlugin()` → `Plugin`\n- **Dependencies:** `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`\n- **Hook:** `afterBuild`\n- **Requirements:**\n  - Store `dev-server-config` in `ctx.data`\n  - Config interface:\n    ```typescript\n    {\n      port: number;              // default 3000\n      routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n      assetPaths: string[];      // from asset-manifest\n      searchIndexPath: string;   // \"/search-index.json\" if exists\n    }\n    ```\n  - Include asset routes (handler: \"asset\") for each asset from asset-pipeline\n  - Include content routes (handler: \"static\") for each HTML file in ctx.output\n  - Handle missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\n---\n\n### 6. PACKAGE.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Available Dependencies:**\n- `marked` - markdown parsing (v17.0.2)\n- `express` - web framework (for dev-server if needed)\n- `@types/marked` - TypeScript types for marked\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` - compile TypeScript via tsc\n- `npm run lint` - run eslint on src/ and tests/\n- `npm test` - run vitest\n\n---\n\n### 7. tsconfig.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Key Settings:**\n- Strict TypeScript mode enabled\n- ES2022 target\n- CommonJS modules (Node16)\n- Output to `./dist`\n- Declaration files generated\n- Compiles only `src/` directory (not tests)\n\n---\n\n### 8. TEST STATISTICS\n\n**Total Tests:** 75 (15 core + 60 plugin tests)\n\n**Tests Per Plugin:**\n- markdown-ext: 8 tests\n- asset-pipeline: 8 tests\n- syntax-highlight: 8 tests\n- taxonomy: 9 tests\n- rss-feed: 8 tests\n- search-index: 7 tests\n- sitemap: 8 tests\n- dev-server: 9 tests\n\n**Validation Requirements:**\n1. `npm test` - all 75 tests must pass\n2. `npm run build` - must compile without errors\n3. `npm run lint` - must be clean (no ESLint errors)\n\n---\n\n### 9. PLUGIN DEPENDENCY GRAPH\n\n```\nWave 1 (Independent):\n  - markdown-ext (no deps)\n  - asset-pipeline (no deps)\n  - syntax-highlight (no deps)\n  - taxonomy (no deps)\n\nWave 2 (Depends on Wave 1):\n  - rss-feed → [markdown-ext, taxonomy]\n  - search-index → [markdown-ext, syntax-highlight]\n\nWave 3 (Depends on Wave 2):\n  - sitemap → [taxonomy, rss-feed]\n  - dev-server → [asset-pipeline, search-index]\n```\n\nThe engine's `resolvePluginOrder()` method uses topological sort to determine execution order and will throw errors if:\n- Circular dependencies are detected\n- Dependencies reference non-existent plugins\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY IMPLEMENTATION NOTES\n\n1. **Plugin Factory Pattern:** Each plugin must export a `createXxxPlugin()` function that returns a `Plugin` object with name, version, dependencies, and hooks.\n\n2. **Shared Data Store:** The `ctx.data` Map allows plugins to share information:\n   - taxonomy → stores `'taxonomy-tags'` for other plugins\n   - asset-pipeline → stores `'asset-manifest'`\n   - dev-server → reads from both and stores `'dev-server-config'`\n\n3. **Hook Execution Order:**\n   - All `beforeBuild` hooks execute in dependency order\n   - All `transformContent` hooks execute in dependency order on all files\n   - All `afterBuild` hooks execute in dependency order\n\n4. **Async Support:** Hooks can be `async` or sync (Promise or void)\n\n5. **HTML Generation:** The markdown-ext plugin should use the `marked` library to convert markdown to HTML, with additional processing for:\n   - Footnotes (custom syntax)\n   - Admonition containers (custom syntax)\n\n6. **Asset Rewriting:** Must distinguish between:\n   - Relative URLs starting with `./` → rewrite to `/assets/FILENAME`\n   - Absolute URLs (http/https) → leave unchanged\n   - Already-rewritten URLs (starting with `/assets/`) → leave unchanged\n\n7. **RSS 2.0 Compliance:** Must generate valid RSS XML with proper CDATA wrapping for HTML content.\n\n8. **Search Index:** Plain text extraction from HTML (strip all tags but preserve content).\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive analysis provides everything needed to implement the 8 plugins successfully!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2aceaf (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36311\n